org.jamwiki.parser

Class TableOfContents

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jamwiki.parser.TableOfContents

  • public class TableOfContents
extends Object
    This class is used to generate a table of contents based on values passed in through the parser.

    • Method Detail

      • addEntry

        public void addEntry(String name,
                     String text,
                     int level)
        Add a new table of contents entry to the table of contents object. The entry should contain the name to use in the HTML anchor tag, the text to display in the table of contents, and the indentation level for the entry within the table of contents.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the entry, to be used in the anchor tag name.
        text - The text to display for the table of contents entry.
        level - The level of the entry. If an entry is a sub-heading of another entry the value should be 2. If there is a sub-heading of that entry then its value would be 3, and so forth.

      • attemptTOCInsertion

        public String attemptTOCInsertion(ParserInput parserInput,
                                  String raw)
                           throws IOException
        This method checks to see if a TOC is allowed to be inserted, and if so returns an HTML representation of the TOC.
        Parameters:
        parserInput - The current parser input configuration object.
        Returns:
        An HTML representation of the current table of contents object, or an empty string if the table of contents can not be inserted due to an inadequate number of entries or some other reason.
        Throws:
        IOException

      • buildUniqueName

        public String buildUniqueName(String name)
        Verify the the TOC name is unique. If it is already in use append a numerical suffix onto it.
        Parameters:
        name - The name to use in the TOC, unless it is already in use.
        Returns:
        A unique name for use in the TOC, of the form "name" or "name_1" if "name" is already in use.

      • getStatus

        public int getStatus()
        Return the current table of contents status, such as "no table of contents allowed" or "uninitialized".
        Returns:
        The current status of this table of contents object.

      • setForceTOC

        public void setForceTOC(boolean forceTOC)

        Parameters:
        forceTOC - Set to true if a TOC is being forced to appear, false otherwise.
